org.grouplens.grapht.util

Interface TypedProvider<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    javax.inject.Provider<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    InstanceProvider, MemoizingProvider

    public interface TypedProvider<T>
extends javax.inject.Provider<T>
    A provider that can report at runtime the type it will provide. This is mostly to allow instance and wrapper providers to pass through type information.
    Since:
    0.6
    Author:
    GroupLens Research

    • Method Detail

      • getProvidedType

        Class<?> getProvidedType()
        Get the type of object that will be provided by this provider. Any object returned from Provider.get() must be of this type. This is used to help the injector refine its types.
        Returns:
        The type of objects that will be provided.
